cs.NA, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.CE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper presents a new model of asynchronous iterations for a time-domain decomposition method, and applies it to solve a numerical problem (European option pricing). 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper focuses on parallel computing and presents numerical experiments performed on a parallel supercomputer. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper presents a new algorithm (asynchronous parareal) for solving a numerical problem. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with a control problem (option pricing) and presents a new method for solving it. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper applies the new method to a finance problem (European option pricing) and presents numerical experiments to illustrate its performance and efficiency.
